        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-07-19 22:08:52.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nDo we really need a new RestconfApiCallNode?  How is this different from restapi-call-node?",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
      {
        "id": "761707261545f75a9bcc7f30764dde05fdf796f9",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1443,
          "name": "Gaurav Agrawal",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "gaurav.agrawal@huawei.com",
          "username": "agrawalgaurav"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2018-07-20 03:05:51.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nHi Dan,\nPlease find the brief comparison and brief on basically what we are trying to achieve:\n\nRESTCONF vs RESTful\nRESTCONF basically describes how to map YANG specification to a RESTful interface thereby enabling basic CRUD operations on a \"hierarchy\" of conceptual resources.\n\nRestconfApiCallNode vs RestApiCallNode\nRestconfApiCallNode aims at using the YANG tooling to achieve automation and to eliminate the need to write Manual JSON/XML template which are to be written with RestApiCallNode for YANG based RESTCONF API's.\nAt the same time it facilitates operation on \"hierarchy of resources\" which in my understanding is not possible today with RestApiCallNode without writing explicit JSON/XML templates for different URLs.",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
